1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. Nf3 Nbd7 5. Bc4 Be7 6. dxe5 ({It is well-known that, without a preliminary central exchange, the sacrifice} 6. Bxf7+ $2 {is incorrect -} Kxf7 7. Ng5+ Kg8 8. Ne6 Qe8 9. Nxc7 Qg6 10. Nxa8 Qxg2 11. Rf1 {and Black is clearly better after} exd4 $1 $36 12. Qxd4 $140 Ne5 13. f3 Nh5 $1 $17 {[%cal Ge7h4]}) (6. Ng5 $6 {is initiating a forced sequence, which is quite similar to the leading text -} O-O 7. Bxf7+ Rxf7 8. Ne6 Qe8 9. Nxc7 Qd8 10. Nxa8 b5 $1 (10... b6 {is also fine, with a probable transposition}) 11. O-O Bb7 {and Black, due to his pair of bishops, has decent chances to seize the initiative, e.g.} 12. f3 b4 13. Ne2 d5 14. f4 Nxe4 15. fxe5 Rxf1+ 16. Qxf1 Qxa8 $132) 6... dxe5 (6... Nxe5 {is an alternative, with equality after} 7. Nxe5 dxe5 8. Qxd8+ Bxd8 $11) 7. Ng5 {At least consequent.} ({Possible is} 7. Qe2 {, but the trade in the center suits better Black -} c6 8. O-O O-O $11 {[%cal Gd8c7]}) 7... O-O 8. Bxf7+ Rxf7 9. Ne6 Qe8 10. Nxc7 Qd8 11. Nxa8 b6 12. Be3 Ba6 13. Nxb6 axb6 $132 *

